  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed advertisement, by reason of its location, size and method of illumination and intermittent display, is harmful to the public safety of the area. As such, the proposal is contrary to policies 6.3 (Assessing the effect of development on transport capacity), 6.9 (Cycling) and 6.10 (Walking) of the London Plan 2016, and policies LP7 (Advertisements), LP42 (Walking and Cycling) LP43 (Transport and Development) of Hackney&#x27;s Local Plan 2020&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposal, by reason of its scale, design, method of illumination and siting in a prominent corner location is considered unsympathetic to the appearance of the building and the character and visual amenity of the locality. The proposal is therefore contrary to policies 7.4 (Local Character) and 7.6 (Architecture) of the adopted London Plan (2016), Policies LP1 (Design) and LP7 (Advertisement) of the adopted Hackney Local Plan (2020) and guidance under the NPPF 2019 (as amended).&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposal, by reason of its size, design, position and illumination would result in significant light overspill which would harm the amenity of the neighbouring residential occupiers. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies 7.4 (Local character) and 7.6 (Architecture) of the London Plan 2016 and policy LP2 (Development and amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
